WEBVTT

00:00.753 --> 00:02.023
Previously on
<i>Bones...</i>

00:02.024 --> 00:04.058
There's a hacker named
Christopher Pelant.

00:04.091 --> 00:06.827
Where are you?
Pretty much anywhere I want to be.

00:06.862 --> 00:08.529
This guy's killed how many people?
Eight.

00:08.564 --> 00:10.398
<i>This guy is worse than anyone</i>

00:10.432 --> 00:11.999
<i>you and I have ever</i>
<i>come across.</i>

00:12.034 --> 00:14.135
Hello, Temperance.
Pelant.

00:14.169 --> 00:16.003
What do you think happened
to poor Chloe Campbell?

00:16.038 --> 00:17.538
I think you killed her.

00:17.573 --> 00:18.906
Wasn't me.
You know who did it.

00:18.941 --> 00:21.909
Uh, same person
who did 187-05-7932,

00:21.944 --> 00:24.545
and 9224-- they were
all killed by one person,

00:24.580 --> 00:25.646
and I think
she's still out there.

00:25.681 --> 00:26.480
You okay, Bones?

00:26.515 --> 00:27.515
The next explosion

00:27.549 --> 00:28.616
will level the
entire building.

00:28.650 --> 00:30.017
Shoot him, Booth.
What?

00:30.052 --> 00:31.319
Shoot him!

00:34.189 --> 00:35.256
And if anything happens
to me, she'll keep

00:35.290 --> 00:37.458
doing what she's doing,

00:37.492 --> 00:39.760
and you'll never
find out who she is.

00:41.663 --> 00:44.665
(heart beating slowly)

00:44.700 --> 00:46.500
(hissing, whirring)

00:54.910 --> 00:57.178
(echoing):
Who's taken these remains?

01:02.117 --> 01:04.218
Who has these remains?!

01:04.253 --> 01:06.454
Who's been in here?!

01:08.757 --> 01:11.392
(gasps) You shouldn't have
shot me, Temperance.

01:11.426 --> 01:13.127
You'll never
find the killer alone.

01:13.161 --> 01:14.528
You'll never find...

01:14.563 --> 01:16.130
You'll never find
the killer alone.

01:16.164 --> 01:17.798
You'll never
find the killer alone.

01:17.833 --> 01:20.401
You hate me.
You hate me... hate me.

01:20.435 --> 01:23.537
No, I don't! No, I don't!
Give me those remains!

01:23.572 --> 01:25.873
Without me... without me...
you'll never find

01:25.907 --> 01:27.108
what connects the victims,
Temperance.

01:27.142 --> 01:28.876
Where are you?!

01:28.910 --> 01:30.745
Where are you?!

01:30.779 --> 01:32.480
(gasps)

01:32.514 --> 01:33.614
(echoing):
Temperance... Temperance...

01:33.649 --> 01:35.082
(gasps)

01:35.117 --> 01:36.450
Temperance, Temperance,
Temperance, Temperance...

01:36.485 --> 01:37.718
(Brennan shrieks)

01:37.753 --> 01:39.453
Temperance, Temperance,
Temperance,

01:39.488 --> 01:40.955
Temperance, Temperance...

01:42.791 --> 01:45.459
(screaming)

01:47.296 --> 01:49.664
(gasping)

01:49.698 --> 01:51.732
(gasps)

01:51.767 --> 01:54.235
(clinking,
clattering, rattling)

01:58.473 --> 02:00.274
(screaming)

02:02.377 --> 02:05.446
(screaming): No!
What? What is it?! What?

02:05.480 --> 02:07.014
What?

02:07.049 --> 02:09.616
It was Pelant, Booth.

02:09.651 --> 02:11.786
Oh. Again?

02:11.820 --> 02:13.754
He had the evidence,
all the bones,

02:13.789 --> 02:15.823
and then I was buried.

02:15.857 --> 02:18.326
It was a dream, right?
He was laughing at me, Booth.

02:18.360 --> 02:18.860
What?

02:18.868 --> 02:21.116
He said that I would
never find the Ghost Killer.

02:21.363 --> 02:23.264
Pelant is dead, right?

02:23.298 --> 02:25.866
I will find the
killer, Booth. I will.

02:25.901 --> 02:27.802
Okay, all right,
I know you will.

02:27.836 --> 02:29.637
It's just,
it was a dream, okay?

02:29.671 --> 02:31.405
You need to get
some rest, all right?

02:31.440 --> 02:33.674
Rest. Come on.
Okay.

02:33.709 --> 02:36.110
Come here.
Okay. Hold me.

02:36.144 --> 02:38.612
Okay... All right...
I got you.

02:38.647 --> 02:40.181
Tighter.
All right.

02:40.215 --> 02:42.717
I'm right here.
It's okay. Shh.

02:42.751 --> 02:44.752
I'm right here.

02:44.786 --> 02:46.487
BRENNAN: I don't understand
why Cam won't believe

02:46.521 --> 02:48.489
the serial killer is real.

02:48.523 --> 02:50.558
Well, it's 'cause there's no
evidence that they're linked.

02:50.592 --> 02:52.293
I mean, there's
nothing conclusive.

02:52.327 --> 02:54.729
Which is why she should
keep the case open.

02:54.763 --> 02:56.697
I need the resources.

02:56.732 --> 03:00.000
You know, you have to admit,

03:00.035 --> 03:01.836
I mean, from the outside,
it does look like

03:01.870 --> 03:04.038
um, Pelant was just,
you know, playing you.

03:04.072 --> 03:06.107
Is that what you believe?

03:06.141 --> 03:07.641
Look, I mean, come on.

03:07.676 --> 03:09.076
You've been poring
over this case for months,

03:09.111 --> 03:10.678
and you haven't come up
with anything.

03:10.712 --> 03:13.314
We can't just, you know,
launch an investigation

03:13.348 --> 03:14.682
on a ghost.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.016
So you don't believe me?

03:16.051 --> 03:17.184
No, it's not that.
I just...

03:17.219 --> 03:18.886
You know what?

03:18.920 --> 03:20.554
I don't want to argue.
It's a beautiful day, huh?

03:20.589 --> 03:23.190
I'm gonna go
get the paper.

03:23.225 --> 03:25.626
(dog barking, birds singing)

03:25.660 --> 03:27.661
Bones, you expecting a package?

03:27.696 --> 03:28.796
No. Why?

03:28.830 --> 03:30.998
Well... one here.

03:37.706 --> 03:40.674
Oh!

03:40.709 --> 03:43.778
No. Wow.

03:47.315 --> 03:51.385
What kind of
sick joke is this?

03:51.420 --> 03:53.788
Someone took great
care in packaging

03:53.822 --> 03:55.256
these remains.

03:55.290 --> 03:56.791
There's a note.

04:02.230 --> 04:05.132
"Please find out
what really happened to me."

