04:15.143 --> 04:17.577
BRENNAN: <i>Based on the shape</i>
<i>of the frontal bone,</i>

04:17.612 --> 04:20.014
the narrow nasal aperture
and the size of the mandible,

04:20.048 --> 04:21.515
the victim was
a Caucasian female.

04:21.550 --> 04:23.117
Aren't you

04:23.151 --> 04:24.518
even the least bit freaked out

04:24.553 --> 04:26.720
that these remains were sent
to your house?

04:26.755 --> 04:28.923
I'm the best forensic
anthropologist in the country.

04:28.957 --> 04:30.925
Wouldn't you want me
examining your remains?

04:30.959 --> 04:32.493
SAROYAN:
I think Angela was

04:32.527 --> 04:34.295
referring more to the mysterious
nature of the delivery.

04:34.329 --> 04:36.263
HODGINS: And the fact
that it was to your home,

04:36.298 --> 04:37.965
not the lab.
BRENNAN: No.

04:37.999 --> 04:39.266
There's too much red tape here.

04:39.301 --> 04:41.068
They may not have
even made it to me.

04:41.102 --> 04:42.503
SAROYAN:
Desiccated skin,

04:42.537 --> 04:45.773
soil... this person was interred
at least a decade.

04:45.807 --> 04:48.642
I'll see what particulates
I can get off this.

04:48.677 --> 04:50.444
Whoa, did you sleep
in those clothes?

04:50.479 --> 04:52.213
What? No.

04:52.247 --> 04:55.149
Uh, apologies, uh,
for being late.

04:55.183 --> 04:56.684
Why are you even here?

04:56.718 --> 04:58.219
I called him when I thought

04:58.253 --> 04:59.787
we might be dealing
with archaeological remains.

04:59.821 --> 05:02.323
Ten years does not classify
these as archaeological.

05:02.357 --> 05:03.958
Well, I'm already here,
so I might as well help out.

05:03.992 --> 05:05.960
I don't need another
forensic anthropologist.

05:05.994 --> 05:07.495
What I need
is an intern.

05:07.529 --> 05:08.696
None of whom are available,

05:08.730 --> 05:09.970
and you need help, Dr. Brennan.

05:09.998 --> 05:11.165
So, boss me around.

05:11.199 --> 05:12.399
I'm ready.

05:12.434 --> 05:14.301
Clean these.

05:22.177 --> 05:25.579
SWEETS: No postmark?
No fingerprints?

05:25.614 --> 05:27.381
It's no surprise--
anyone who digs someone up

05:27.415 --> 05:28.883
and delivers them like takeout--

05:28.917 --> 05:30.243
of course they're going
to be careful, Sweets.

05:30.244 --> 05:30.968
You okay?

05:30.969 --> 05:33.254
No, I'm not okay,
okay, Sweets? I'm not.

05:33.255 --> 05:34.722
Someone delivered
a dead body to my house.

05:34.756 --> 05:36.123
How can I be okay?

05:36.157 --> 05:38.259
Right. Sorry.
It's just, it seems...

05:38.293 --> 05:39.693
And Bones is having
nightmares again.

05:39.728 --> 05:41.462
Oh.
Yeah.

05:41.496 --> 05:43.163
She thinks there's another
serial killer out there.

05:43.198 --> 05:44.765
Because that's what Pelant
told her before he died?

05:44.799 --> 05:45.199
Yes.

05:45.224 --> 05:47.184
He just wanted her to
think that he was necessary.

05:47.235 --> 05:49.703
Right? And she feels the need
to prove that he's not.

05:49.738 --> 05:52.473
Okay, Pelant is dead.
The guy is dead.

05:52.507 --> 05:54.108
Why can't anyone
just accept that?

05:54.142 --> 05:55.876
I understand.
Okay, then, help me with the case.

05:55.911 --> 05:57.511
All right, look at the case.

05:57.546 --> 05:59.213
Maybe it'll take Bones's mind
off this craziness.

05:59.247 --> 06:02.883
Okay. Well, the remains are
painstakingly wrapped in cloth.

06:02.918 --> 06:04.585
Right? And the note implies

06:04.619 --> 06:06.287
that the truth of her
death was never known, so,

06:06.321 --> 06:07.601
whoever did this took a big risk

06:07.622 --> 06:09.356
because they care
about the victim.

06:09.391 --> 06:11.492
But how do you know
that this is not some psycho

06:11.526 --> 06:12.927
playing some sick games
with her?

06:12.961 --> 06:15.663
Unfortunately, we don't.

